### đźŞ™ NIBMX-Au Tokenization ([vault.mjs](file:///c:/Users/OMEN/Documents/kibx/api/_routes/vault.mjs) + [tokens.mjs](file:///c:/Users/OMEN/Documents/kibx/api/_routes/tokens.mjs))

Two token systems exist in the codebase:

#### System A â€” User Self-Service ([vault.mjs](file:///c:/Users/OMEN/Documents/kibx/api/_routes/vault.mjs) lines 152-287)
| Feature | Endpoint |
|---------|----------|
| Mint token from vault balance | `POST /tokens/mint` |
| Transfer token to user (by email) | `POST /tokens/transfer` |
| Redeem token â†’ vault gold | `POST /tokens/redeem` |
| Token balance | `GET /tokens/balance` |
| Token market info (public) | `GET /tokens/market` |

- **Token ID format:** `NIBMX-Au-{base36_timestamp}-{random}`
- **Backing:** 1:1 gold-backed (deducted from vault on mint, credited on redeem)
- **Token lifecycle:** `active` â†’ `transferred` / `redeemed` / `burned`

#### System B â€” Maker-Checker Governance ([tokens.mjs](file:///c:/Users/OMEN/Documents/kibx/api/_routes/tokens.mjs))
| Feature | Endpoint |
|---------|----------|
| Initiate mint (Maker â€” Officer 1) | `POST /tokens/mint` or `/mint` |
| Review mint (Checker â€” Officer 2) | `PUT /tokens/mint/:id/review` or `/mint/:id/review` |
| Burn tokens (physical gold redemption) | `POST /tokens/burn` or `/burn` |
| List mints (admin/user scoped) | `GET /tokens/mints` or `/mints` |
| Token balance | `GET /tokens/balance` or `/balance` |
| Token overview (admin dashboard) | `GET /tokens/overview` or `/overview` |

- **Dual-control:** Maker â‰  Checker enforced (403 if same person)
- **Separate balance tracking:** `token_balances` table (balance, total_minted, total_burned, total_traded)

> [!IMPORTANT]
> There are duplicate route definitions between [vault.mjs](file:///c:/Users/OMEN/Documents/kibx/api/_routes/vault.mjs) and [tokens.mjs](file:///c:/Users/OMEN/Documents/kibx/api/_routes/tokens.mjs) â€” both define `/tokens/mint`, `/tokens/burn`, `/tokens/balance`, etc. These should be consolidated into a single router.

